com.here.platform.location.integration.optimizedmap.navigationattributes.javadsl

Interface IntersectionInternalCategories


  • public interface IntersectionInternalCategories
    The type of intersection for a segment range. It is used to indicate whether a driver will perceive the situation as a single intersection. May be used for manoeuvre explication and map display.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static IntersectionInternalCategory INDESCRIBABLE
      This value indicates a manoeuvre that cannot be explained in one command.
      static IntersectionInternalCategory INTERSECTION_INTERNAL
      Segments that provide internal structure and road connectivity within an intersection.
      static IntersectionInternalCategory MANOEUVRE
      Identifies a segment or a sequence of segments which may be grouped into a single guidance instruction.

    • Field Detail

      • INTERSECTION_INTERNAL

        static final IntersectionInternalCategory INTERSECTION_INTERNAL
        Segments that provide internal structure and road connectivity within an intersection.

      • MANOEUVRE

        static final IntersectionInternalCategory MANOEUVRE
        Identifies a segment or a sequence of segments which may be grouped into a single guidance instruction.

      • INDESCRIBABLE

        static final IntersectionInternalCategory INDESCRIBABLE
        This value indicates a manoeuvre that cannot be explained in one command. A graphic may be needed to illustrate the turn. In these situations a driver may need to go right to make a left turn.
